    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00baC/ 220\u00baC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Take your<strong> beef joint[s]</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and chop into large chunky rounds</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>carrot discs </strong>and <strong>leek rounds</strong> to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a generous splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, a small knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around them to form a tightly sealed parcel[s] and add to a baking tray (or two)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for an initial 10 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potatoes </strong>and chop in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-8 min or until slightly tender</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Pat dry your <strong>beef joint[s] </strong>with kitchen paper</p><p>Rub over your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>dried thyme</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coated beef</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated beef </strong>to the pan and cook for 2-3 min or until slightly browned on all sides \u2013 this is your <strong>browned beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender, remove the tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>(reserve the bowl for later!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>browned beef </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] on the top shelf of the oven and cook for 18-20 min or until the beef is cooked through and slightly pink inside</p><p>Tip: Prefer no pink meat? Cook your beef for 3-5 min longer!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has had 20 min, remove it from the oven, transfer to a clean chopping board and leave to rest for 3 min \u2013 this is your <strong>thyme roast beef</strong></p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 3 min or until the potatoes are roasted and golden and the veg is tender</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is nearly ready, boil half a kettle</p><p>Combine your <strong>gravy base </strong>with 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>in the reserved bowl, whisk thoroughly</p><p>Put it in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 30-40 secs or until thickened and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>rested beef </strong>finely</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-roast-beef-with-buttered-veg-and-roasties/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sliced beef</strong> with the <strong>roasties</strong>, <strong>buttered veg </strong>and your <strong>mint sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
